{
  "texts": [
    "proposed to modify the training data by explicitly identifying gender-neutral words and using them to adjust the genderspecific words in the embedding data [123].",
    "For example, they replace the word \"he\" with \"she\" and vice versa in the text data, creating balanced examples of each gender association.",
    "They also use gender-neutral word pairs (no association with a particular gender), such as \"doctor\" and \"nurse\", to help the model learn a more balanced representation of gender-related concepts [123].",
    "In this regard, Kamiran et al.",
    "proposed a 'massaging' method that used and extended a Naïve Bayesian classifier to rank and learn the best candidates for re-labeling [26,63]."
  ]
}